---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Viṣṇu Sahasranāma Verse 14 — One Verse, 80 Readings"
  description="88 characters, 80 linguistically valid decompositions, 3 to 9 divine names. How Sanskrit compound-splitting is itself a theological act."
  lang={lang}
>
  <section class="section stack">
    <h1 class="section-title">Viṣṇu Sahasranāma — Verse 14</h1>
    <p class="vsn-subtitle">The First Nine Names: One Verse, Three Theologies</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="prose vsn-prose">

      <h2>The Verse</h2>

      <div class="vsn-verse-block">
        <div class="vsn-script-label">Devanāgarī</div>
        <div class="vsn-verse-line">विश्वं विष्णुर् वषट्कारो भूतभव्यभवत्प्रभुः ।</div>
        <div class="vsn-verse-line">भूतकृद् भूतभृद् भावो भूतात्मा भूतभावनः ॥</div>

        <div class="vsn-script-label">Telugu</div>
        <div class="vsn-verse-line">విశ్వం విష్ణుర్ వషట్కారో భూతభవ్యభవత్ప్రభుః |</div>
        <div class="vsn-verse-line">భూతకృద్ భూతభృద్ భావో భూతాత్మా భూతభావనః ||</div>

        <div class="vsn-script-label">IAST</div>
        <div class="vsn-verse-line vsn-iast">viśvaṃ viṣṇur vaṣaṭkāro bhūtabhavyabhavatprabhuḥ |</div>
        <div class="vsn-verse-line vsn-iast">bhūtakṛd bhūtabhṛd bhāvo bhūtātmā bhūtabhāvanaḥ ||</div>
      </div>

      <hr>

      <h2>Reading 1: Nine Names</h2>
      <h3>Maximum Splitting — Each Divine Function is Distinct</h3>

      <div class="vsn-table-wrap">
        <table class="vsn-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th class="vsn-num">#</th><th>Devanāgarī</th><th>Telugu</th><th>IAST</th><th>English</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">1</td><td class="vsn-dev">विश्वं</td><td class="vsn-tel">విశ్వం</td><td>viśvaṃ</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Universe / The All-pervading</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">2</td><td class="vsn-dev">विष्णुः</td><td class="vsn-tel">విష్ణుః</td><td>viṣṇuḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Pervader (vi + √ṣ, to pervade)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">3</td><td class="vsn-dev">वषट्कारः</td><td class="vsn-tel">వషట్కారః</td><td>vaṣaṭkāraḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Embodiment of the sacrificial call Vaṣaṭ</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">4</td><td class="vsn-dev">भूतभव्यभवत्प्रभुः</td><td class="vsn-tel">భూతభవ్యభవత్ప్రభుః</td><td>bhūtabhavyabhavatprabhuḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Lord of past, future, and present</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">5</td><td class="vsn-dev">भूतकृत्</td><td class="vsn-tel">భూతకృత్</td><td>bhūtakṛt</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Creator of all beings</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">6</td><td class="vsn-dev">भूतभृत्</td><td class="vsn-tel">భూతభృత్</td><td>bhūtabhṛt</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Sustainer of all beings</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">7</td><td class="vsn-dev">भावः</td><td class="vsn-tel">భావః</td><td>bhāvaḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">Existence itself / Pure Being</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">8</td><td class="vsn-dev">भूतात्मा</td><td class="vsn-tel">భూతాత్మా</td><td>bhūtātmā</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Self (Ātman) of all beings</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">9</td><td class="vsn-dev">भूतभावनः</td><td class="vsn-tel">భూతభావనః</td><td>bhūtabhāvanaḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Cause of all beings' becoming</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>This is BORI's reading and Śaṅkara's tradition. It is the <strong>unique maximum</strong> — the only decomposition that yields 9 names. Every pair that <em>can</em> be split <em>is</em> split.</p>

      <hr>

      <h2>Reading 2: Seven Names</h2>
      <h3>One Compound Merged — Creation and Sustenance as One Act</h3>

      <div class="vsn-table-wrap">
        <table class="vsn-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th class="vsn-num">#</th><th>Devanāgarī</th><th>Telugu</th><th>IAST</th><th>English</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">1</td><td class="vsn-dev">विश्वं</td><td class="vsn-tel">విశ్వం</td><td>viśvaṃ</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Universe</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">2</td><td class="vsn-dev">विष्णुः</td><td class="vsn-tel">విష్ణుః</td><td>viṣṇuḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Pervader</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">3</td><td class="vsn-dev">वषट्कारः</td><td class="vsn-tel">వషట్కారః</td><td>vaṣaṭkāraḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Vaṣaṭ Embodiment</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">4</td><td class="vsn-dev">भूतभव्यभवत्प्रभुः</td><td class="vsn-tel">భూతభవ్యభవత్ప్రభుః</td><td>bhūtabhavyabhavatprabhuḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">Lord of past, future, present</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">5</td><td class="vsn-dev">भूतकृद्भूतभृद्भावः</td><td class="vsn-tel">భూతకృద్భూతభృద్భావః</td><td>bhūtakṛdbhūtabhṛdbhāvaḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">Creator-Sustainer-Existence (triple dvandva)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">6</td><td class="vsn-dev">भूतात्मा</td><td class="vsn-tel">భూతాత్మా</td><td>bhūtātmā</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Self of all beings</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="vsn-num">7</td><td class="vsn-dev">भूतभावनः</td><td class="vsn-tel">భూతభావనః</td><td>bhūtabhāvanaḥ</td><td class="vsn-eng">The Cause of becoming</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>Name 5 merges <em>bhūtakṛt</em> (creator), <em>bhūtabhṛt</em> (sustainer), and <em>bhāva</em> (existence) into a single triple dvandva compound. The theological implication: creation, sustenance, and existence are not three separate divine functions but one undivided act.</p>

      <hr>

      <h2>Reading 3: Three Names</h2>
      <h3>Maximally Monistic — ALL Functions as ONE</h3>

      <div class="vsn-mega">
        <span class="vsn-mega-dev">विश्वंविष्णुः</span>
        <span class="vsn-mega-tel">విశ్వంవిష్ణుః</span>
        <span class="vsn-mega-eng">1. The All-pervading Viṣṇu</span>
      </div>

      <div class="vsn-mega">
        <span class="vsn-mega-dev">वषट्कारोभूतभव्यभवत्प्रभुः</span>
        <span class="vsn-mega-tel">వషట్కారోభూతభవ్యభవత్ప్రభుః</span>
        <span class="vsn-mega-eng">2. The Vaṣaṭ who is Lord of all times</span>
      </div>

      <div class="vsn-mega">
        <span class="vsn-mega-dev">भूतकृद्भूतभृद्भावोभूतात्माभूतभावनः</span>
        <span class="vsn-mega-tel">భూతకృద్భూతభృద్భావోభూతాత్మాభూతభావనః</span>
        <span class="vsn-mega-eng">3. Creator-Sustainer-Existence-Self-Cause — ALL as ONE</span>
      </div>

      <p>The third name is the mega-compound: creator-sustainer-existence-self-cause — five divine functions collapsed into a single unbroken word. This is Advaita in grammar. The divine does not have five attributes. The divine <em>is</em> one reality that appears as five when you split the compound.</p>

      <div class="vsn-discovery">
        <h2>The Discovery</h2>
        <p>88 characters. 80 linguistically valid decompositions. 3 to 9 names.</p>

        <div class="vsn-table-wrap">
          <table class="vsn-table vsn-table--dark">
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Names</th><th>Readings</th><th>Character</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>3</td><td>1</td><td>Maximally monistic — all functions collapsed</td></tr>
              <tr><td>4</td><td>7</td><td></td></tr>
              <tr><td>5</td><td>8</td><td></td></tr>
              <tr><td>6</td><td>13</td><td></td></tr>
              <tr><td>7</td><td>22</td><td>Most ambiguity — the theological sweet spot</td></tr>
              <tr><td>8</td><td>7</td><td>Seven ways to merge exactly one pair</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>9</strong></td><td><strong>1</strong></td><td><strong>Unique maximum — every split taken</strong></td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="vsn-closing">
        <p>The text does not choose. The commentator chooses.</p>
        <p>The choice <strong>IS</strong> the theology.</p>
        <p class="vsn-closing-names">
          <strong>9 names</strong>: each divine function is distinct.<br>
          <strong>7 names</strong>: creation and sustenance are one act.<br>
          <strong>3 names</strong>: ALL functions of the divine are one reality.
        </p>
        <p>Same 88 characters. Same Sanskrit. Same verse.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .vsn-subtitle {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
  }

  .vsn-prose {
    max-width: 56rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* verse block */
  .vsn-verse-block {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 2;
  }

  .vsn-script-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .vsn-script-label:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .vsn-verse-line {
    font-family: var(--font-serif), serif;
  }

  .vsn-iast {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* tables */
  .vsn-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .vsn-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .vsn-table th {
    background: var(--color-text);
    color: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 0.625rem 0.75rem;
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .vsn-table td {
    padding: 0.625rem 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .vsn-table tr:nth-child(even) {
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .vsn-num {
    font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    width: 2rem;
  }

  .vsn-dev { font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .vsn-tel { font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .vsn-eng { font-style: italic; color: var(--color-muted); }

  /* mega compounds */
  .vsn-mega {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .vsn-mega-dev {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .vsn-mega-tel {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .vsn-mega-eng {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  /* discovery section */
  .vsn-discovery {
    background: var(--color-text);
    color: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 2rem;
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .vsn-discovery h2 {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .vsn-table--dark th {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-text) 80%, white 20%);
  }

  .vsn-table--dark td {
    border-bottom-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-text) 70%, white 30%);
    color: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .vsn-table--dark tr:nth-child(even) {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-text) 90%, white 10%);
  }

  /* closing */
  .vsn-closing {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 2;
  }

  .vsn-closing strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .vsn-closing-names {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    line-height: 2.2;
  }
</style>
